You need to make a few changes to your code to make the preferred location field a multiple select. Here's the updated code:

```
jsx
<Controller 
  name="location" 
  control={control} 
  render={({ field }) => (
    <FormControl fullWidth>
      <InputLabel id="location-label">location</InputLabel>
      <Select 
        {...field} 
        multiple 
        labelId="location-label" 
        id="location" 
        label="location"
        value={selectedLocation}
        onChange={(e: SelectChangeEvent<string[]>) => {
          setSelectedLocation(e.target.value);
          field.onChange(e.target.value);
        }}
      >
        {locations.map((name) => (
          <MenuItem key={name} value={name}>
            {name}
          </MenuItem>
        ))}
      </Select>
    </FormControl>
  )}
/>
```

In the above code:

- We added a state `selectedLocation` to store the selected locations.
- We set the `multiple` prop to `true` in the `Select` component.
- We updated the `value` prop of the `Select` component to `selectedLocation`.
- We updated the `onChange` event handler to update both the `selectedLocation` state and the form field value.

Now, the preferred location field should work as a multiple select.
